{"id":165,"date":"2023-07-10T23:23:50","date_gmt":"2023-07-11T06:23:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/?page_id=165"},"modified":"2024-06-15T13:51:49","modified_gmt":"2024-06-15T20:51:49","slug":"interrogatives-i","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/imabi.org\/interrogatives-i\/","title":{"rendered":"Interrogatives I"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Interrogatives: Who, What, When, Where, &amp; Why?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In English, we create questions with what are colloquially called &#8220;wh-words.&#8221; Although there are quite a few of these words in English, it is customary to view &#8220;who,&#8221; &#8220;what,&#8221; &#8220;when,&#8221; &#8220;where,&#8221; and &#8220;why&#8221; as the basic five.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In grammar, these words are called &#8220;interrogatives.&#8221; These words in English, though, have two fundamental kinds of usage. The following examples demonstrate this with the words &#8220;when&#8221; and &#8220;where.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>i. When did he go home?<br>ii. I like it when you dance.<br>iii. Where do you live.<br>iv. The place where I bought my dog is really nice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Interrogatives (\u7591\u554f\u8a5e) &#8211; literally in Japanese as &#8220;part of speech for questioning&#8221; &#8211; as the name implies, are words which revolve around questioning. In English, there is rule that interrogatives go at the start of a sentence and\/or clause. In Japanese, there is no such rule. To put this in perspective, consider the following:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>v. Who went with you to the park?<br>vi. Last night when I came home from work, [who was it to that you were talking on the phone with]?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In v. and vi., &#8220;who&#8221; must be at the start of their respective independent clauses. However, this as you will see in this lesson, is not the case in Japanese. As we learn about the rules of Japanese interrogatives, try to superimpose your understanding of English interrogatives on to them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this lesson, we will learn about the basic question words of Japanese, but to simplify things, we will only look at how interrogatives behave in polite speech, then we will revisit each interrogative individually later on to see how speech register affects them.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Interrogatives in Polite Speech<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first interrogatives that we will be going over are &#8220;who,&#8221; &#8220;what,&#8221; &#8220;when,&#8221; &#8220;where,&#8221; and &#8220;why.&#8221; In Japanese, these words can appear in more places in the sentence than in English. This difference happens to affect various factors in how they are used. In the following chart, take note of the differences between interrogatives used at the start of a sentence and interrogatives used at the end of a sentence.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>\u00a0Interrogative<\/td><td>\u00a0Start of a Sentence<\/td><td>\u00a0End of a Sentence<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u00a0Who<\/td><td>\u8ab0\u304c\u2026\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><td>\u2026\u306f\u8ab0\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u00a0What<\/td><td>\u4f55\u304c&#8230;\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><td>&#8230;\u306f\u4f55\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u00a0When<\/td><td>\u3044\u3064\uff08\u304c\uff09&#8230;\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><td>&#8230;\u306f\u3044\u3064\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u00a0Where<\/td><td>\u3069\u3053\u304c&#8230;\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><td>&#8230;\u306f\u3069\u3053\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>\u00a0Why<\/td><td>\u4f55\u6545&#8230;\uff5b\u306e\u30fb\u3093\uff5d\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><td>&#8230;(\u306e)\u306f\u4f55\u6545\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The placement of interrogatives is determined by how much emphasis you are placing on the individual words in the sentence. The closer to the front of a sentence something is, the more emphasis is placed on it. This principle helps determine the nuances in the examples below designed to give you a thorough range of grammatical complexity that comes about simply from the patterns above. \u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>1a.\u00a0<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u793e\u9577<rt>\u3057\u3083\u3061\u3087\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>1b.\u00a0<ruby>\u793e\u9577<rt>\u3057\u3083\u3061\u3087\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Who is the company president?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ex. 1a. would only be used in the sense of \u201c<em>who<\/em>\u00a0is the company president?\u201d It would only be used when asking about who the company president is in a conversation where said person would not be present. This is unlike 1b. which could be used to ask who the company president is out of a group of people visible\/near the speaker and listener(s).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>2.\u00a0<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u597d<rt>\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304d\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<br>Who do you like?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>3.\u00a0<ruby>\u59bb<rt>\u3064\u307e<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306b<ruby>\u4f3c<rt>\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3066\u308b\u3068<ruby>\u601d<rt>\u304a\u3082<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304b\uff1f<br>Who do you think my wife looks like?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>4.\u00a0<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3068<ruby>\u4e00\u7dd2<rt>\u3044\u3063\u3057\u3087<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306b<ruby>\u4f4f<rt>\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3093\u3067\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Who do you live together with?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>5.\u00a0<ruby>\u4e00\u756a\u597d<rt>\u3044\u3061\u3070\u3093\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304d\u306a<ruby>\u79d1\u5b66\u8005<rt>\u304b\u304c\u304f\u3057\u3083<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Who is your favorite scientist?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>6.\u00a0<ruby>\u62c5\u5f53\u8005<rt>\u305f\u3093\u3068\u3046\u3057\u3083<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Who will be(come) the manager?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>7.\u00a0<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u5909<rt>\u304b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308f\u3063\u305f\u306e\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What exactly has changed?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>8. \u304a<ruby>\u571f\u7523<rt>\u307f\u3084\u3052<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c\u3044\u3044\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What would be good for souvenirs?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>9.\u00a0<ruby>\u5c65<rt>\u306f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304d<ruby>\u7269<rt>\u3082\u306e<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c\u3044\u3044\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What would be good for footwear?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>10.\u00a0<ruby>\u4eca\u65e5<rt>\u304d\u3087\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306e<ruby>\u65e5<rt>\u3072<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What day<sup data-fn=\"a4a0986c-0d5b-4f96-9109-885824bfca31\" class=\"fn\"><a href=\"#a4a0986c-0d5b-4f96-9109-885824bfca31\" id=\"a4a0986c-0d5b-4f96-9109-885824bfca31-link\">1<\/a><\/sup> is it today?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>11. \u3048\u3001<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Uh, what?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>12a. \u304a<ruby>\u4ed5\u4e8b<rt>\u3057\u3054\u3068<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>12b. \u4f55\u306e\u4ed5\u4e8b\u3092\u3057\u3066\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>12a. What is your job?<br>12b. What line of work are you in?&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>13. \u304a<ruby>\u540d\u524d<rt>\u306a\u307e\u3048<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What is your name?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>14.\u00a0<ruby>\u8da3\u5473<rt>\u3057\u3085\u307f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What are your hobbies?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As is true of all interrogatives, \u3044\u3064 is an example of an adverbial noun, being grammatically rendered either as an adverb or as a noun depending on the surrounding grammatical context. When \u3044\u3064 is used more so like a noun, it is very similar in nuance to &#8220;what time (period)?&#8221; \u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>15.\u00a0<ruby>\u4f4f\u5b85<rt>\u3058\u3085\u3046\u305f\u304f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3092<ruby>\u6709\u5229<rt>\u3086\u3046\u308a<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306b<ruby>\u8cb7<rt>\u304b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3046<ruby>\u6642\u671f<rt>\u3058\u304d<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3044\u3064\u304c\u3044\u3044\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What time is good to lucratively buy a home?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>16.\u00a0<ruby>\u96db\u4eba\u5f62<rt>\u3072\u306a\u306b\u3093\u304e\u3087\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3092<ruby>\u98fe<rt>\u304b\u3056<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b<ruby>\u6642\u671f<rt>\u3058\u304d<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3044\u3064\u3054\u308d\u304c<ruby>\u826f<rt>\u3044<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>About what time would be alright to display hina dolls?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>17. \u3053\u306e\u30b5\u30d7\u30ea\uff08\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\uff09\u306f\u3001<ruby>\u98f2<rt>\u306e<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3080\u30bf\u30a4\u30df\u30f3\u30b0\u304c\u3044\u3064\u304c\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u306a\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<br>As for this supplement, what timing would be best to drink it?<br><br>18. \u30a8\u30a2\u30b3\u30f3\u306f\u3044\u3064\u304c<ruby>\u5b89<rt>\u3084\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>When is it that air conditioning is cheap?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>19.\u00a0<ruby>\u8acb\u6c42<rt>\u305b\u3044\u304d\u3085\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3044\u3064\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>When will billing be?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>20. \u3044\u3064<ruby>\u4ed5\u4e0a<rt>\u3057\u3042<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c\u308a\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>When will you be finished?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>21. \u30a4\u30c1\u30b4\u306f\u3044\u3064<ruby>\u751f<rt>\u306a<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b<sup data-fn=\"aa8d5183-439f-4a01-9551-4044308833ee\" class=\"fn\"><a href=\"#aa8d5183-439f-4a01-9551-4044308833ee\" id=\"aa8d5183-439f-4a01-9551-4044308833ee-link\">2<\/a><\/sup>\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f<br>When do strawberries ripen?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>22. \u30b1\u30fc\u30bf\u30a4\u306e<ruby>\u7dca\u6025\u5730\u9707\u901f\u5831<rt>\u304d\u3093\u304d\u3085\u3046\u3058\u3057\u3093\u305d\u304f\u307b\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3044\u3064<ruby>\u9cf4<rt>\u306a<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>When does the mobile emergency earthquake alert go off?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>23.\u00a0<ruby>\u5fa9\u8208<rt>\u3075\u3063\u3053\u3046<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3044\u3064<ruby>\u6210<rt>\u306a<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b\u306e\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>When will restoration come into fruition?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>24. \u300c\u3044\u3064\u304c<ruby>\u7a7a<rt>\u3042<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u3066\u307e\u3059\uff1f\u300d\u300c<ruby>2<rt>\u306b<\/rt>\u9031\u9593\u5f8c<rt>\u3057\u3085\u3046\u304b\u3093\u3054<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u7a7a<rt>\u3042<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u3066\u307e\u3059\uff01\u300d<br>\u201cWhat time is available?\u201d \u201cTwo weeks from now is available!\u201d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Grammar Note<\/strong>: With the use of\u00a0\u304c, it is apparent that openings in schedules are being referred to as opposed to one&#8217;s personal availability per se. \u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>25.\u00a0<ruby>\u4eca<rt>\u3044\u307e<\/rt><\/ruby>\uff08\u306f\uff09\u3001\u3044\u3064\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br><em>Ima (wa), itsu desu ka?\u00a0<br><\/em>What point in time is it now?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Sentence Note<\/strong>: One can imagine Ex. 25 being used by someone from the future confused as to what point in time he has traveled to. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>26. \u3044\u3064\u30de\u30ec\u30fc\u30b7\u30a2\u306b<ruby>\u6765<rt>\u304d<\/rt><\/ruby>\u307e\u3057\u305f\u304b\u3002<br>When did you come to Malaysia?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>27.\u00a0<ruby>\u96fb\u6c60<rt>\u3067\u3093\u3061<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3001\u3044\u3064\u3001<ruby>\u8ab0<rt>\u3060\u308c<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u767a\u660e<rt>\u306f\u3064\u3081\u3044<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\u304b\u3002<br>As for the battery, when and who invented it?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>28. \u30b9\u30df\u30b9\u3055\u3093\u306f\u3069\u3053\u3067<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3092<ruby>\u58ca<rt>\u3053\u308f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\u304b\u3002<br>What did Mr. Smith break and where?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>29.\u00a0<ruby>\u65e5\u672c<rt>\u306b\u307b\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306e\uff5b<ruby>\u4f55<rt>\u306a\u306b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u30fb\u3069\u3053\uff5d\u304c<ruby>\u597d<rt>\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304d\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>{What about\/where} in Japan do you like?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>30.\u00a0<ruby>\u6570\u5b66<rt>\u3059\u3046\u304c\u304f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306e\u3069\u3053\u304c<ruby>\u597d<rt>\u3059<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304d\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What part about math do you like?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>31.\u00a0<ruby>\u4f4f\u6240<rt>\u3058\u3085\u3046\u3057\u3087<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3069\u3053\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What<sup data-fn=\"4775be99-1067-4fe1-8138-68010f5b58c5\" class=\"fn\"><a href=\"#4775be99-1067-4fe1-8138-68010f5b58c5\" id=\"4775be99-1067-4fe1-8138-68010f5b58c5-link\">3<\/a><\/sup> is your address?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>32. \uff5b\u30c8\u30a4\u30ec\u30fb\u304a<ruby>\u624b\u6d17<rt>\u3066\u3042\u3089<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\uff5d\u306f\u3069\u3053\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Where is the bathroom\/restroom?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>33. \u306a\u305c<ruby>\u8857<rt>\u307e\u3061<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3078<ruby>\u884c<rt>\u3044<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3063\u305f\u306e\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why did you go to town?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>34. \u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30cb\u306e\u304a\u306b\u304e\u308a\u3001\u3069\u3053\u304c<ruby>\u7f8e\u5473<rt>\u304a\u3044<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3057\u3044\u3068<ruby>\u601d<rt>\u304a\u3082<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>As for convenience store rice balls, where are they really good at?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>35.\u00a0<ruby>\u98db\u884c\u6a5f<rt>\u3072\u3053\u3046\u304d<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306e<ruby>\u5ea7\u5e2d<rt>\u3056\u305b\u304d<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3069\u3053\u304c\u3044\u3044\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>What seats on a(n air)plane are good?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>36.\u00a0<ruby>\u90f5\u4fbf\u5c40<rt>\u3086\u3046\u3073\u3093\u304d\u3087\u304f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3069\u3053\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Where is the post office?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When\u00a0\u306a\u305c is placed towards the front of a sentence, the predicate usually ends in\u00a0\uff5e\uff5b\u3093\u30fb\u306e\uff5d\u3067\u3059\u304b, which is done so to hone in on the reason for the situation at hand. The contracting\u00a0of \u306e to\u00a0\u3093 is indicative of the spoken language. When \uff5e\uff5b\u3093\u30fb\u306e\uff5d\u3067\u3059\u304b follows nouns or adjectival nouns, remember to insert \u306a, as this ending follows the \u9023\u4f53\u5f62.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>37.\u00a0<ruby>\u725b<rt>\u3046\u3057<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u3001\u306a\u305c<ruby>\u6bce\u65e5\u4e73<rt>\u307e\u3044\u306b\u3061\u3061\u3061<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u51fa<rt>\u3067<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why do cows produce milk every day?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>38.\u00a0<ruby>\u706b\u5c71<rt>\u304b\u3056\u3093<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306f\u306a\u305c<ruby>\u5674\u706b<rt>\u3075\u3093\u304b<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3059\u308b\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why do volcanoes erupt?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>39. \u306a\u305c<ruby>\u540d\u8a5e<rt>\u3081\u3044\u3057<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306a\u3093\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why is it a noun?\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Under the same principles, if\u00a0\u306a\u305c is at the end of the sentence, a noun phrase has to precede it. If the phrase is a full sentence, then the particle\u00a0\u306e needs to be used to make it into a noun before\u00a0\u306a\u305c can create the question. In this situation,\u00a0\u306e shouldn&#8217;t ever be contracted.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>40.\u00a0<ruby>\u4eba\u3005<rt>\u3072\u3068\u3073\u3068<\/rt><\/ruby>\u304c<ruby>\u795e<rt>\u304b\u307f<\/rt><\/ruby>\u306b<ruby>\u7948<rt>\u3044\u306e<\/rt><\/ruby>\u308b\u306e\u306f\u306a\u305c\u3067\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why do people pray to God\/the gods.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>41.\u00a0<ruby>\u592a<rt>\u3075\u3068<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3063\u305f\u306e\u306f\u306a\u305c\u3060\u3068<ruby>\u601d<rt>\u304a\u3082<\/rt><\/ruby>\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304b\u3002<br>Why do you think it is you got fat?<\/p>\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-footnotes\"><li id=\"a4a0986c-0d5b-4f96-9109-885824bfca31\">Day as in a special day, not a day of the week.  <a href=\"#a4a0986c-0d5b-4f96-9109-885824bfca31-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71671\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><li id=\"aa8d5183-439f-4a01-9551-4044308833ee\">While \/naru\/ is a great example of a multifaceted homophone, without the use of the particle \u306b, it would have to be interpreted as \u751f\u308b (to ripen), \u9cf4\u308b (to sound\/ring), or \u6210\u308b (to come into fruition).\u00a0  <a href=\"#aa8d5183-439f-4a01-9551-4044308833ee-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71672\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><li id=\"4775be99-1067-4fe1-8138-68010f5b58c5\">Contrary to English, the word for &#8220;where&#8221; needs to be used in asking what someone&#8217;s address is, as &#8220;address&#8221; is not perceived as a &#8220;what&#8221; but as a location. <a href=\"#4775be99-1067-4fe1-8138-68010f5b58c5-link\" aria-label=\"\u811a\u6ce8\u53c2\u71673\u306b\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\">\u21a9\ufe0e<\/a><\/li><\/ol>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Interrogatives: Who, What, When, Where, &amp; Why? In English, we create questions with what are colloquially <a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/imabi.org\/interrogatives-i\/\">\u7d9a\u304d\u3092\u8aad\u3080 <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">&#8220;Interrogatives I&#8221;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":158153075,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":